Initial git commit
Test Commit
Planned a bit of the sentence generator
Renamed class and added new instructions
Added two new corpus resources, both of these are specific databases to be used for the sentence generators

Added functionality to noun and verb classes. They can both return the word that they contain in an annotated form, also added functionality in the sentence generator constructor so that it can load stuff from the Noun Chain Database.
Added functionality to load up the VerbChain

Got the sentence generator to return an adequate noun and verb, works with one method. Need to restructure and ensure that the code works more efficiently. Perhaps create a method for commonly used code

SentenceGenerator NV sentences are complete, accomodated NounClass and VerbClass to deal with string identifiers for the nounclassfinder method, still need to implement some rules for 1a and 2a noun classes as well as 14.
Sucessfully obtained the verb and used to obtain a noun list, need to initialise the noun and account for ALLs and exceptions
created a helper method to ensure that we can grab a noun from the database when called
Sentence generator works, need to update VerbClass modifier methods for correct sentences
Senetence generator complete, needed to create pluraliser for sentence exercise
Multiple changes: Completed sentence pluraliser for NV, changed verb pluraliser and prefix modifier, removed multiple trace statements throught the code

Fixed bugs that threw null pointers. Corpus pruned, does not include functionality for NVV sentences, need to implement better more code to handle exceptions that arise from that. Solved problem relating to negative argument
Corrected generator bugs and flaws in spelling and rule implementation, pluralisers now work with capital letters, change output format, next step is to generate questions for passing into the UI
Created new code specifically for the generation of a textfile to be passed into Soham's diffculty assessment and UI

Sentence Pluraliser exercise for Soham's system works, driver demo was updated to test, removed redundant code, and took away automated annotation mechanism, now we have a manual annotation system, specific to each class
Got Noun Pluraliser Gen working for Sohams format, Got Sentence Generator Working for Sohams format, Created new driver class
Verb Plural Gen working for Sohams system, need to work on the interface for accepting booleans
Driver and all classes work for demo
